FBIS3-60881 "jptot001__l94129" JPRS-TOT-94-001-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 7 January 1994 CENTRAL EURASIA GEORGIA Regional Armed Units Engaged To Fight Terrorists LD2712141493 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1342 GMT 27 Dec 93 LD2712141493 Moscow ITAR-TASS Language: English Article Type:BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tengiz Djibuti] [Text] Moscow December 27 TASS -- Regional armed units are being engaged to fight terrorists in Georgia, an official from the Georgian Interior Ministry told ITAR-TASS by telephone on Monday. The units were created by a decree of Eduard Shevardnadze and will help local law enforcement bodies to disarm illegal armed groups and to carry out operations against criminal gangs and mafia clans on the territory of the republic. TASS learned from a source in the headquarters resolving emergency situations in western Georgia that for the last week only police had halted activities of four big armed gangs which had been for a long time attacking local residents, policemen and administrators.
